Pierce et al have designed a set of <termsem="GO:0006310"> recombination </term> substrates for measuring the level of homologous <termsem="GO:0006310"> recombination </term> in vivo ( Fig. 1 ) [ 25 ] .
The DNA substrate contains a pair of mutated GFP genes ( GFP encodes the easily detected green fluorescent protein ) , one of which contains a restriction site for I-SceI , a yeast intron encoded <termsem="GO:0004519"> <termsem="independent_continuant"> endonuclease </term> </term> with an 18 base pair recognition site .
